{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KzNttGQMRjPYLz3Sws5W4W","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here's what was done and why:\n\n**Root cause:** The replica set was initiated with only 2 voting members (`mongo-rs-0`, `mongo-rs-1`). With 2 votes, reaching majority requires both nodes — losing either one makes elections impossible. The arbiter pod was running but not registered in the replica set config.\n\n**Fix applied:**\n1. `setDefaultRWConcern` — MongoDB 5.0+ requires an explicit cluster-wide write concern before any reconfig that changes the implicit majority (adding a non-data-bearing arbiter shifts the data-bearing majority from 2→1).\n2. `rs.addArb(\"mongo-arb-0.mongo-arb.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\")` — added the arbiter as `_id: 2`, `arbiterOnly: true`.\n\n**Result:**\n- 3 voting members: PRIMARY (`mongo-rs-0`), SECONDARY (`mongo-rs-1`), ARBITER (`mongo-arb-0`)\n- Majority is now 2 of 3 — the set can survive losing one member and still elect a primary\n- No storage added (arbiters hold no data)\n- `app.test` still has 3 documents — data intact"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":143,"cache_read_input_tokens":44044,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":143},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"80fd3b04-038f-4876-afb7-6d5a9449e9df","uuid":"f51471a4-b476-4766-9c24-3406a315107d","request_id":"req_011CcQd14cn9coBZuYR76vHJ"}
